gujarati.context:
Amareliye puno pachaa, makhan aamad khojaa sujaan;
Kanbee bhakt parvat chhe naam, ehe aadi Amareli gaa.

In English:
Unending life is the gain of toil; 
Devoted soul is the name of this mountain village from ancient times.

The translation is:

Waveri pithe janashali jehe, bhakt moolu babariyo tehe;
Jadav karanu bago kunbhar, vese gama ghanaala mozhara.

Here is the translation:

Waso mulo ne veero rabari, vase likhaale bhave murari;
Ugo mato ro kadvao kahay, kathi bhakt goradka may.

Here is the translation:

Haribhakt che baai kunvar, ehadi jan damanagar;
Kambhi bhakta dayo haradas, jan thauka thalse vaas.

becomes:

He is devoted to God, a princess of good family, from Damanagar; 
The devotee has taken refuge at God's door, the people are amazed.

Manukunvar ne Dholibai, Dwij Vase e Traps Maini;
Kanbai Pati Viro Naam, Bhakta Khoja e Talaaje Gam.

(Man's wife Dholibai is in my house; the virtuous person is in trouble in that very village;
The name of the brave ones is Kanbhai's husband, the devotees are searching for it in that very farm.)
